Wow. But good to know that Hannah went on. I have to wonder if people  
follow their bodies to the graveyard and then don&#39;t know what the  
hell to do next. Especially kids. Examples of kid EVP in grave yards  
is so plentiful that it&#39;s heartbreaking. Maybe they get there and  
others who are already hanging out there tell them its where they  
should stay, because they seem to have some kind of social life going  
on there, too.

One example that blew me away starts with a taper asking when anyone  
died. A male voice replies with a full date, something like,  
&quot;September 5, 1952,&quot; then a long pause, &quot;Do you think they heard us?&quot;

Ann

